[% INCLUDE 'intranet-bottom.inc' %]

[% BLOCK display_messages %]
    [% UNLESS messages AND messages.size %][% RETURN %][% END %]
    <div class="dialog alert">
        [% IF messages.size > 1 %]
            <h3 style="padding-left: 1em;">Please try again</h3>
            <ol>
        [% ELSE %]
            <h3>Please try again</h3>
        [% END %]
        [% FOREACH m IN messages %]
            [% IF messages.size > 1 %]<li>[% ELSE %]<p>[% END %]
            [% SWITCH m %]
                [% CASE 'using_db_user' %]
                    You are using the database user. You should never use this user. Use a superlibrarian user instead.
                [% CASE 'no_koha_git_dir' %]
                    This tutorial is supposed to be used inside Koha.
                [% CASE 'commit_does_not_start_with_bug_number' %]
                    The commit message must start with 'Bug 18584: '
                [% CASE 'commit_does_not_contain_spaces' %]
                    The first line of the commit message must specify that you are removing trailing spaces
                [% CASE 'first_line_too_long' %]
                    The first line of the commit message is too long (more than 80 characters)
                [% CASE 'too_many_files_modified' %]
                    You should have one and only one file modified
                [% CASE 'too_many_lines_modified' %]
                    You should have one and only one line modified
                [% CASE 'commit_message_does_not_contain_filename' %]
                    The first line of the commit message must specify the filename you touch.<br/>
                    <strong>Note:</strong> Most of the time you do not need to specify it. In our case it is different: several commits will be needed to fix all the trailing spaces. To differentiate the commits it will be preferable to highlight the filename in the commit message.
                [% CASE 'commit_message_does_not_contain_test_plan' %]
                    The commit message must contain a test plan.<br/>
                    <strong>Note:</strong> In this situation the test plan will be very short. A simple line "Open the file and confirm that the trailing spaces are gone" would be enough.<br/>
                    For a more complex patch we will expect a step-by-step plan to confirm the issue is fixed.
                [% CASE 'branch_without_bugnumber' %]
                    You must work on a branch that contain the number of the bug, something like <code>bug_18584</code>
                [% CASE 'too_many_commits_diff_with_master' %]
                    There are too many commits of difference between <code>origin/master</code> and your local branch.<br/> Are you sure your local branch is up-to-date with <code>origin/master</code>?
                [% CASE 'not_executed' %]
                    You did not execute the QA script, or the number of commits you tested were wrong.<br/>
                    You need to execute the following command: <code>qa -c 1 -v 2</code>.
                [% CASE 'report_not_nso' %]
                    The bug report is not in the 'Needs Signoff' status. You should update it if your patch is attached.
                [% CASE 'patch_not_applied' %]
                    The patch is not applied correctly!
                [% CASE 'patch_not_signed_off' %]
                    The patch is not signed off!
                [% CASE 'report_not_so' %]
                    The bug report is not in the 'Signed Off' status. You should update it if your signed-off patch is attached.
                [% CASE %][% m %]
            [% END %]
            [% IF messages.size > 1 %]</li>[% ELSE %]</p>[% END %]
        [% END %]
        [% IF messages.size > 1 %]</ol>[% END %]

        [% UNLESS not_a_step %]
            [% IF substep %]
                <a href="/cgi-bin/koha/how-to.pl?step=[% step %]&substep=[% substep %]&verify=1" id="next_step" class="btn btn-default btn-sm"><i class="fa fa-refresh"></i> Retry</a>
            [% ELSE %]
                <a href="/cgi-bin/koha/how-to.pl?step=[% step %]&verify=1" id="next_step" class="btn btn-default btn-sm"><i class="fa fa-refresh"></i> Retry</a>
            [% END %]
            [% IF next_substep %]
                <a href="/cgi-bin/koha/how-to.pl?step=[% next_step %]&substep=[% next_substep %]" id="next_step" class="btn btn-default btn-sm"> Skip this step <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
            [% ELSE %]
                <a href="/cgi-bin/koha/how-to.pl?step=[% next_step %]" id="next_step" class="btn btn-default btn-sm"> Skip this step <i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
            [% END %]
        [% END %]
    </div>
[% END %]

[% BLOCK attach_patch %]
    <p>
        To attach the last patch of the branch you can use:
    </p>

    <pre><span class="prompt"></span> git bz attach -e 18584 HEAD</pre>

    <ol>
        <li><code>-e</code>: To switch the status of the bug report to <code>Needs Signoff</code> (among other things)</li>
        <li><code>18584</code>: It is of course the bug number of the bug report where you want to attach your patch</li>
        <li><code>HEAD</code>: In git jargon it means the latest commit from the branch you are in</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="note">
        Note: Sometimes you will want to attach several patches to a bug report in a row. It is easily feasible modifying the last parameter using git intervals.<br/>
        For instance: <code>HEAD~2..HEAD</code> will attach the last 2 patches.<br/>
        In this syntax the last <code>HEAD</code> is optional. So you could also use <code>HEAD~2..</code> as an equivalent.
    </div>
[% END %]

